                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Europe/Berlin"
                    },
                    "body": "I implemented those suggested changes locally and did notice a performance drop of 20% as more reallocations still come in quite expensive, even with in-place resizing provided by {{jemalloc}}. Also the overhead of calling {{nallocx}}\u00a0is in our case larger then we actually save by fully using the allocated space (wastage is always <4KiB). Thus the above mentioned optimizations still sound good theroretically to me but don't seem to bring a practical benefit.\n\nClosing this as it is not a pressing issue. We can tackle this once someone has a usecase.",
